<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-09-25T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-09-25T11:00:00-05:00" n="160" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d160">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">841D.24/27: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Ireland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gray</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-25T12:00:00-04:00">September 25, 1940—noon</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>66. Department’s No. 64, September 20, 6 p.m. An additional lot of
                                rifles has been declared surplus and is being sold to the British.
                                It is suggested that the Irish Government may wish to instruct
                                Brennan to discuss this matter further with Lothian and Purvis.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>